ata-lemma=\"\">δὲ\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"ἀρχαία\" data-n=\"300\" data-lemma=\"\">ἀρχαία\u003C/span> Τ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"ab-l9-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">9\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"χορὸν\" data-n=\"320\" data-lemma=\"\">χ]ορὸν\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"θεῶν\" data-n=\"325\" data-lemma=\"\">θεῶν\u003C/span> [\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"ab-l10-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">10\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΤΑΙΚΥΚ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"ab-l11-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">11\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"πολύστειοι\" data-n=\"355\" data-lemma=\"\">πολύ?]στειοι\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"ποταμοί\" data-n=\"360\" data-lemma=\"\">(\u003Cem>scil.\u003C/em> ποταμοί)\u003C/span> [\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",{"author":3,"date":4,"citedRange":258,"ptr":259,"ref":260,"inscriptionDate":4,"title":2,"citation":5,"uri":6},"1079-1082",{"target":114},{"_":116,"target":116},{"file":262,"uri":262,"title":263,"status":264,"editionAuthor":13,"type":265,"objectType":269,"material":273,"condition":26,"layoutDesc":277,"handNote":281,"date":426,"places":430,"geo":433,"provenance":211,"provenanceGeo":435,"country":72,"region":73,"settlement":64,"repository":438,"idno":439,"textLang":441,"tmNumber":443,"facsimile":444,"letterHeights":449,"publications":453,"zotero":460,"keywords":467,"html":471,"bibl":472,"bulletinDateSort":117,"citedRangeSort":475,"languageSort":79,"materialSort":274,"typeSort":266},"ISic003367","I.Sicily inscription 003367",{"_":12},{"_":266,"ana":267,"ref":268},"oracle","#function.oracle","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/429.html",{"_":270,"ana":271,"ref":272},"stele","#object.stele","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/250",{"_":274,"ana":275,"ref":276},"limestone","#material.stone.limestone","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/66.html",{"layout":278},{"p":279,"rs":280,"damage":26},"The text is neatly laid out with a clear left margin on a single field below the moulding; divisions in the text at lines 5-6 and 25-26 are marked by paragraphoi.",{"_":31,"ana":32,"ref":33},{"lettering":282,"dimensions":418},[283,284],"Letters are regular and deeply cut, with slightly prounced serifs at the end of strokes. Alpha is broad with straight bar, and occasional tendency to apex at the top; beta has equal sized, closed, shallow loops; epsilon has shorter middle bar and slightly outward pointing top and bottom bars; zeta is formed by a vertical with horizontals top and bottom; theta is slightly ovoid in form, with a complete cross bar; kappa has short, equal length tails; Mu has slightly inward leaning first and final strokes, with the middle strokes meeting well above the middle of the line; nu has a shorter right hand stroke, with the lower angle above the line; omicron is small and mid-line; Pi has a slightly shorter right hand vertical; rho has small closed eye, of varying form (rounded or elongated); sigma has slightly outward facing top and bottom storkes and the middle strokes are sometimes rounded at the join; upsilon has shallow spreading upper strokes; phi has a rounded eye, with extended vertical stroke; chi is consistnly slightly larger than other characters; omega open, slightly smaller and above the line, with horizontal tails. A horizontal stroke is visible above and the left of the first letter of lines 6 and 26.",{"_":285,"ref":286},"\n                                    Types list:\n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n               